On December 3, 2021, the President signed into law H.R. 6119, known as the "Further Extending Government Funding Act." This law includes a short-term continuing resolution that provides fiscal year 2022 appropriations to Federal agencies until February 18, 2022. The appropriations are meant to fund ongoing projects and activities of the Federal Government. Additionally, the law includes supplemental appropriations to support the ongoing needs of Afghanistan evacuees. Furthermore, the law extends several expiring authorizations. The President expressed gratitude to Speaker Nancy Pelosi, Majority Leader Chuck Schumer, Minority Leader Mitch McConnell, Chairman Patrick Leahy, Vice Chairman Richard Shelby, and Chair Rosa DeLauro for their contributions to this legislation.